        public MonetaryAmount convertToEntityAttribute(BigDecimal dbData) {...}
    }

If you need to store the currency as well, then you should use Vlad Mihalceas https://github.com/vladmihalcea/hypersistence-utils:

    @CompositeType(MonetaryAmountType.class)
    private MonetaryAmount amount;

the database should hold both an amount and a currency:

    &lt;column name=&quot;amount&quot; type=&quot;decimal(19,4)&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;column name=&quot;currency&quot; type=&quot;char(3)&quot;/&gt;

If you need different names (e.g. when you have several amounts in your table), then go for @AttributeOverride:

    @AttributeOverride(name = &quot;amount&quot;, column = @Column(name = &quot;amount_in_question&quot;))
    @AttributeOverride(name = &quot;currency&quot;, column = @Column(name = &quot;amount_in_question_currency&quot;))
    @CompositeType(MonetaryAmountType.class)
    private MonetaryAmount amountInQuestion;

